args:
When Volk kidnaps a renowned bishop and
takes his life, Ciella decides to infiltrate the
Church. Harle then appears and gives her
what she seeks: historical documents that
record a secret regarding the seventh scion.
Why would it be in a church?
Because the one who took it from the\nroyal palace handed it off to the bishop.\nThis information is good, I assure you.
You will forgive me if I find myself\nloath to trust you so readily.
Maybe you ought to get yourself a mirror.\nBut either way, we don't have to trust each\nother—we just have to play our parts.
Then let us make hasty our start. Oh,\nand one more thing: Do not hold me back.
We beg you, tell us the aims of the\ngoddess! Why would someone as\nwonderful as the priest have to die?!

Stand back! Back with you, I say!
The bishop is a busy man who does
not have time to answer the queries
of you slack-jawed lot!
Soft, good knight. One of my duties—\nperhaps the most important one—is to\noffer guidance to the lost among our flock.
Good people, your beloved Father Harold\nhas passed on, and I join your number in\ngrieving for his terrible loss.

He was a rare man—the kind who forsook
materialism and was eminently virtuous.
Indeed, he offered succor to the weak by
donating his personal wealth to his parish.
Yes, but why did he have to DIE?\nWhat cold-hearted cur could strike\ndown such a good and noble man?

The culprit has yet to be apprehended,
but I know they will receive their just
punishment—for the eyes of the Goddess
cannot be led astray.
Never forget, my children, that such hard\ntimes are the true test of our faith.
Now, let us grieve as one and pray\nfor dear Father Harold's soul.
May you find peace, Father Harold...
That penurious priest can't stop being\na bother to me even when he's located\nbeneath six feet of good earth.
It's been a long time, Bishop.
I told you never to enter\nmy private chambers!
Come now, it's only fitting I drop by every\nnow and again considering all the little\n＂requests＂ you ask me to do for you.

Also, I was impressed by the show of grief
you put on over the death of a man whose
life YOU ordered snuffed out. You should
abandon the priesthood for the stage!

The man had to die. This religion is merely
a tool to control the people, yet he
genuinely believed in it, and had
even begun to criticize the Church.
Did you not see how the people adored\nhim during today's funerary service?\nNo, this was a thing most necessary.
Ha ha ha! Oh, but you're always harvesting\nthe hopes of the weak like that, aren't you?\nHow irremissible...
Say now, what do you think you're doing?!\n...No! Help me! Someone, HEEEELP!
You there! Unhand His Grace at once!
I think not. It's time for us to take a\nlittle jaunt.
They leapt out the window! After him!\nSave the bishop!
Is it money you seek, you rapacious fiend?!

You would know all about rapaciousness—
for are you not the man who stuffed his
purse so full of the parish's contributions
that it became bulging and distended?
I do what I do for the sake of the the\nChurch's stability, as well as society's!
There's no escape now, villain!\nHand over the bishop!
Oh, very well. If you want him so badly,\nyou may have him. She's likely found\nwhat she was looking for by now anyway.
Regret. Atone. And feel the pain\nof those who lack strength.
Think of this as punishment. Or better yet,\ndivine retribution! Aaaah ha ha ha ha!
Stop! Come back!\nYou'll pay for this!
Bishop! Bishop, please!\n...It's too late. He's gone.
H-help! Emergency! The church is on fire!
By Ilia, what is HAPPENING tonight...?
＂Good information,＂ was it? Pah! There's\nnot a shred of paper here worth my time.
And now the fires rage all around.\nHow truly desperate these times are.
I have what you seek right here.
Hmm. It seems I wasn't the first\nwith interest in this room.
Terrifically sorry for the late introduction,\nCiella. It is a pleasure to meet you.
Are you familiar with me, sir?

A sylvan who rose to the rank of Paladyns
at a young age before fleeing the Church?
Yes, I'd say you're something of a well-
known quantity around here.
I'm honored. And in that case, I trust you\nwill hand over to me what you carry?
It will save me the trouble of slaying you\nand looting your corpse—although I might\nslay you regardless if the mood so strikes.
Ah, but you certainly are one of his\nassociates. Who would think such violent\npassions lie beneath such surface beauty?

But yes, you may certainly have these!
The first paper is a historical document
from the Alberian royal family, while the
second is a treaty relevant to the first.
The entirety of the truth about the seventh\nscion is contained within these writings.\nDo give them a careful look, mmm?
Well, aren't you a generous fellow?\nI simply MUST know who you are.
I am but a man who finds the height of joy\nin sowing seeds of chaos throughout the\nworld and observing how they grow.
What an utterly tasteless passion.\nI think I shall be going now.
And now, the necessary props have safely\nmade their way into the hands of this\ndrama's leading players.
It grows ever more difficult to wait for\nthe curtain to rise on this fascinating\ndrama in the capital!
